column1: Appendix 9.1 List of all Arctic vascular plant species (with PAF code number) and their distribution in the 21 Arctic floristic provinces and 5 subzones based on Elven (2007). Distribution outside the Arctic in the neighbouring boreal or boreal-alpine zone is given under "N". Presence of indigenous/native species is indicated by a frequency value (r/R = rare, s/S = scattered; f/F = frequent; X presence without frequency value); presence of introduced species by an asterix (* for stabilized introductions, ** for casual introductions); absence by ""; presence uncertain by "?". Borderline Arctic species that are present only in the southernmost part of Subzone E are indicated by "b" (highlighted in green). Arctic endemic species are indicated in grey highlight.
